<TITLE> Bangladesh start SAFF campaign in style </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)--Bangladesh started their sixth SAFF Championship campaign in style with a 4-1 thrashing of Bhutan in their first match at Bangabandhu National Stadium on Friday. The hosts dominated the match right from the word go, finding the net twice on the either side of the break. The first goal came from defender Pranotosh in the 12th minute, and 11 minutes later Enamul Haque doubled the margin. Bhutan were awarded a penalty, from which Endug reduced the margin. Enamul, however, restored the two-goal lead in the second half before Zahid Hossain Emily put the result of the match beyond any doubt in the 72nd minute . Finance minister AMA Muhith inaugurated the tournament at a simple ceremony before the match. Earlier, in the inaugural match, Sri Lanka defeated Pakistan 1-0 Midfielder Chathura Gunaratne scored the winner in the 24th minute from the spot. Sri Lanka were reduced to 10 men in the 79th minute when defender Dumida Wasanthaka Hettiarachchi was sent off on his second bookable offence. They were down to nine men in the next minute when Sanjaya Pradeep Kumara got his marching orders. Pakistan dominated the proceedings but failed to score from a penalty in the dying moments. Striker Adnan Farooq Ahmed saw his scorching shot from the spot sail over. bdne
